<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1438,1422,1945]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,550,1493,1519]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Distribution and ecology:—</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[549,672,1493,1519]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[687,820,1493,1519]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, and western 
<collectingCountry box="[986,1083,1493,1519]" name="Panama" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Panama</collectingCountry>
. On steep slopes along forest margins, landslides, and roadbanks, forming thickets in open disturbed sites, often mixed with other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,333,1570,1596]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Gleicheniaceae</taxonomicName>
, at 
<quantity box="[373,537,1570,1596]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" unit="m" value="1950.0" valueMax="2800.0" valueMin="1100.0">1100–2800 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1438,1422,1945]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,307,1609,1635]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Notes:—</emphasis>
This species belongs to a group of four closely related species, which also include 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nakai" authorityYear="1950" baseAuthorityName="Rosenst." box="[1278,1428,1609,1634]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hastulatus">
<emphasis box="[1278,1428,1609,1634]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">S. hastulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chrysler" authorityYear="1944" baseAuthorityName="Christ" box="[151,325,1648,1673]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orthocladus">
<emphasis box="[151,325,1648,1673]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">S. orthocladus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chrysler" authorityYear="1944" baseAuthorityName="Baker" box="[394,567,1648,1673]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[394,567,1648,1673]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">S. intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They all have scales restricted to the buds and rhizomes, hastulate, (in some species) short-petiolate segments, accessory segments on the pinna bases, 2- or 3-forked veinlets on the auriculate segment bases, obscure veinlets, abaxial blade papillae in most specimens, slightly to strongly undulate segment margins, and ovate, entire, translucent to slightly matte scales. All four species co-occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,279,1802,1828]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and often 
<taxonomicName box="[403,541,1802,1828]" form="mixed" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" rank="form">form mixed</taxonomicName>
populations. Morphologically they grade into each other, with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Copeland" authorityYear="1947" baseAuthorityName="J. Bommer ex Christ" box="[1282,1435,1803,1828]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="retroflexus">
<emphasis box="[1282,1435,1803,1828]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">S. retroflexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chrysler" authorityYear="1944" baseAuthorityName="Baker" box="[201,369,1841,1866]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[201,369,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">S. intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the most distinct forms and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nakai" authorityYear="1950" baseAuthorityName="Rosenst." box="[736,886,1841,1866]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hastulatus">
<emphasis box="[736,886,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">S. hastulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chrysler" authorityYear="1944" baseAuthorityName="Christ" box="[944,1114,1841,1866]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orthocladus">
<emphasis box="[944,1114,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">S. orthocladus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as intermediate forms. It is conceivable that the latter are hybrids between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Copeland" authorityYear="1947" baseAuthorityName="J. Bommer ex Christ" box="[704,859,1880,1905]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="retroflexus">
<emphasis box="[704,859,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">S. retroflexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chrysler" authorityYear="1944" baseAuthorityName="Baker" box="[916,1083,1880,1905]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[916,1083,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">S. intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but more detailed studies are needed.
</paragraph>
